MULTICAST CHAT WITH IMPERSONATION PREVENTION
============================================

Multicast chat with impersonation prevention.

Demonstrate the "layer" concept within communication.

Provide development patterns for multi-protocol processing.

Demonstrate logging pattern.

   Terminal
       |
       |
       V
      Chat     Registration
        \        /
         |      |
         V      V
         Ethernet
            |
            |
            V
         Physical


EXECUTION
---------

> - Windows
$ - *NIX

By being in specific directory:

> cd [location of multicast_chat parent]
> python -m multicast_chat [args]

$ cd [location of multicast_chat parent]
$ python -m multicast_chat [args]

By modifying python path:

> set PYTHONPATH=[location of multicast_chat parent]
> python -m multicast_chat [args]

$ PYTHONPATH=[location of multicast_chat parent] \
    python -m multicast_chat [args]

Your own project in different location:

> set PYTHONPATH=[location of my_multicast_chat parent];[location of network-course]
> python -m multicast_chat [args]

$ PYTHONPATH=[location of my_multicast_chat parent];[location of network-course] \
    python -m my_multicast_chat [ars]

Use --help to see usage example of minimal usage:

> python -m multicast_chat --mac-local=04:c8:80:89:4e:51 --name=user1
